<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 05-12-43 - Fan Blade Replacement for Borg Warner DD-26 (Code 12TSG), DD-30 (Code 12TSJ), SD-65 (Code
        12TST) Viscous Fan Drives on 3600, 3800, 4700,4800, 4900, IC and FE Bus Models Built Between January 1, 1998 and
        March 1, 2004
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi051243" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>05-12-43</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>November, 2005</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Fan Blade Replacement for Borg Warner DD-26 (Code 12TSG), DD-30 (Code 12TSJ), SD-65 (Code 12TST)
                Viscous Fan Drives on 3600, 3800, 4700,4800, 4900, IC and FE Bus Models Built Between January 1, 1998
                and March 1, 2004
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <distribution dealer="yes" fleet="yes" bodybuilder="yes" isis_cd="yes"/>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3600
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2000</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>3800
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2004</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4700
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2001</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4800
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2001</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4900
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2001</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>IC Bus
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2004</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>FE Bus
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>01/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>03/01/2004</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>12TSG</ucode>
                <ucode>12TSJ</ucode>
                <ucode>12TST</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>All vehicles built with Borg Warner DD-26 (Code 12TSG), DD-30 (Code 12TSJ), SD-65 (Code 12TST) fan
                    drives use steel fans. When replacing a fan or a fan drive it is important that the correct fan is
                    installed on the fan drive. If a non-metallic (plastic/nylon) fan is installed on these fan drives,
                    it may result in two types of failure:
                </para>
                <seqlist>
                    <item>
                        <para>The clutch will not operate correctly, affecting activation of the fan at the required
                            temperature and may result in fan drive failure.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>The engine side of the fan drive housing may crack (Figure 1) when an incorrect fan blade
                            is mounted to the fan drive. The fan may not seat correctly against the fan drive housing
                            and tightening the mounting nuts can result in cracks in the fan drive housing (Figure 1).
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
                <figure id="f0512431" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0512431.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                             scalefitheight="328px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Engine Side of Fan Drive with Cracks Indicated by Arrows</caption>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
    </tsi>
</isis>
